Synchronous VS Asynchronous
Synchronous
    A synchronous request blocks the clients until operation completes i.e browser is not unresponsive.
    In such case, javascript engine of the browser is blocked.
Asynchronous(AJAX web-application Model)
    An Asynchronous request doesn't block the client l.e browser is responsive. At that time,user can perform another operations


What is AJAX
-
Ajax is not a programming language.

Ajax just uses a combination of:
1.A broweser built-in XMLHttpRequest Object
2.javascript And HTML DOM(to display or use the data)
*****************************************
3.XML or JSON
    For carrying data to and from server.JSON is like XML but short and faster than XML.


